ZH: 墨水用完了，我得去买一瓶。
EN: The ink is running out, I have to go buy a bottle.

ZH: 这支钢笔的墨水特别好。
EN: The ink in this fountain pen is really good.

ZH:我不小心把墨水洒到了桌子上。
EN: I accidentally spilled ink on the table.

ZH: 墨水盒里装着蓝色的墨水。
EN: The ink cartridge is filled with blue ink.

ZH: 墨水溢出来了，弄脏了我的书包。
EN: The ink leaked out and stained my backpack.

ZH: 这是一种防水的墨水。
EN: This is a waterproof ink.

ZH: 我的毛笔需要更换墨水。
EN: My calligraphy brush needs a refill of ink.

ZH: 你用来写字的墨水是什么颜色的？
EN: What color is the ink you use for writing?

ZH: 墨水的味道总是让人回忆起童年。
EN: The smell of ink always brings back memories of childhood.

ZH:这支笔墨水灰白，透彻。
EN: The pen has greyish-white and translucent ink.

ZH: 我喜欢用墨水给信件润色。
EN: I like to use ink to add color to letters.

ZH: 孩子们用墨水在纸上涂鸦。
EN: The kids doodle with ink on paper.

ZH: 墨水的质地决定了字迹的美观度。
EN: The texture of the ink determines the beauty of the writing.

ZH: 墨水在古代被用来写字和绘画。
EN: Ink was used for writing and painting in ancient times.

ZH: 墨水在书法和绘画中发挥着重要作用。
EN: Ink plays an important role in calligraphy and painting.

ZH: 墨水的种类有很多，你要选择适合自己的。
EN: There are many types of ink, you need to choose the one that suits you.

ZH:我用墨水写了一封情书。
EN: I wrote a love letter with ink.

ZH: 墨水的颜色深浅取决于浓度。
EN: The depth of the ink color depends on its concentration.

ZH: 墨水干了之后才能折叠纸张。
EN: Fold the paper only after the ink has dried.

ZH: 墨水池里的黑色液体有一种诱人的气味。
EN: The black liquid in the inkwell has a tempting scent.
